This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with creating effective information curator recommendation models. It also touches upon fairness properties, which could place it in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Additionally, the use of machine learning algorithms for personalized recommendations could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with issues related to fairness, which could place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) sub-category. Finally, the use of a real-world Twitter dataset could place it in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SOC) sub-category.
